definition.value: a glaucoma AE that has elevated intraocular pressure (EIOP) with single topical agent for intervention; no visual field deficit
a glaucoma AE that has elevated intraocular pressure causing early visual field deficits; multiple topical or oral agents indicated; limiting instrumental activities of daily living

a glaucoma AE that has elevated intraocular pressure causing marked visual field deficits (e.g., involving both superior and inferior visual fields); operative intervention indicated; limiting self care activities of daily living
a glaucoma AE that has blindness (20/200 or worse) in the affected eye
an anaphylaxis AE that has symptomatic bronchospasm, with or without urticaria; parenteral intervention indicated; allergy-related edema/angioedema; hypotension
a retinal detachment AE that has exudative and visual acuity 20/40 or better
a retinal detachment AE that has rhegmatogenous or exudative detachment; operative intervention indicated; decline in vision (worse than 20/40 but better than 20/200)
a retinal detachment AE that has blindness (20/200 or worse) in the affected eye
a hemolysis AE that has laboratory evidence of hemolysis only (e.g., direct antiglobulin test; DAT; Coombs'; schistocytes; decreased haptoglobin)
a hemolysis AE that has evidence of hemolysis and greater than or equal to 2 gm decrease in hemoglobin.
a hemolysis AE where transfusion or medical intervention is indicated (e.g., steroids)
an anal fistula AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function
an anal fistula AE that has severely altered GI function; tube feeding, TPN or hospitalization indicated; elective operative intervention indicated
an atrial tachycardia AE where IV medication is indicated
an atrial tachycardia AE that has life-threatening consequences; incompletely controlled medically; cardioversion indicated
a cholecystitis AE that has severe symptoms; radiologic, endoscopic or elective operative intervention indicated
an autoimmune disorder AE that is asymptomatic; serologic or other evidence of autoimmune reaction, with normal organ function; intervention not indicated
an autoimmune disorder AE that has evidence of autoimmune reaction involving a non-essential organ or function (e.g., hypothyroidism)
an autoimmune disorder AE that has autoimmune reactions involving major organ (e.g., colitis, anemia, myocarditis, kidney)
a spleen disorder AE that has incidental findings (e.g., Howell-Jolly bodies); mild degree of thrombocytosis and leukocytosis
a spleen disorder AE when prophylactic antibiotics are indicated
a burn AE that requires medical intervention; minimal debridement indicated
a burn AE that requires moderate to major debridement or reconstruction indicated
a papulopustular rash AE that has papules and/or pustules covering less than 10% body surface area which may or may not be associated with symptoms of pruritus or tenderness

a papulopustular rash AE that has papules and/or pustules covering 10-30% body surface area, which may or may not be associated with symptoms of pruritus or tenderness; associated with psychosocial impact; limiting instrumental activities of daily living

a papulopustular rash AE that has papules and/or pustules covering greater than 30% body surface area, which may or may not be associated with symptoms of pruritus or tenderness; limiting self-care activities of daily living; associated with local superinfection with oral antibiotics indicated

a papulopustular rash AE that has papules and/or pustules covering any % body surface area, which may or may not be associated with symptoms of pruritus or tenderness and are associated with extensive superinfection with IV antibiotics indicated; life-threatening consequences
an acute coronary syndrome AE that has symptomatic, progressive angina; cardiac enzymes normal; hemodynamically stable
an acute coronary syndrome AE that has symptomatic, unstable angina and/or acute myocardial infarction, cardiac enzymes abnormal, hemodynamically stable
an acute coronary syndrome AE that has symptomatic, unstable angina and/or acute myocardial infarction, cardiac enzymes abnormal, hemodynamically unstable
an aortic valve disease AE that has asymptomatic valvular thickening with or without mild valvular regurgitation or stenosis by imaging
an aortic valve disease AE that has symptomatic; moderate regurgitation or stenosis by imaging
an aortic valve disease AE that has symptomatic; severe regurgitation or stenosis by imaging; symptoms controlled with medical intervention
an aortic valve disease AE that has life-threatening consequences; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., valve replacement, valvuloplasty)
an asystole AE that has periods of asystole; non-urgent medical management indicated
a constrictive pericarditis AE that has symptomatic heart failure or other cardiac symptoms, responsive to intervention
a constrictive pericarditis AE that has refractory heart failure or other poorly controlled cardiac symptoms
a mitral valve disease AE that has asymptomatic valvular thickening with or without mild valvular regurgitation or stenosis by imaging
a mitral valve disease AE that has asymptomatic; moderate regurgitation or stenosis by imaging
a mitral valve disease AE that has symptomatic; severe regurgitation or stenosis by imaging; symptoms controlled with medical intervention
a mitral valve disease AE that has life-threatening consequences; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., valve replacement, valvuloplasty)
a pulmonary valve disease AE that has asymptomatic valvular thickening with or without mild valvular regurgitation or stenosis by imaging
a pulmonary valve disease AE that has asymptomatic; moderate regurgitation or stenosis by imaging
a pulmonary valve disease AE that has symptomatic; severe regurgitation or stenosis by imaging; symptoms controlled with medical intervention
a pulmonary valve disease AE that has life-threatening consequences; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., valve replacement, valvuloplasty)
a tricuspid valve disease AE that has asymptomatic valvular thickening with or without mild valvular regurgitation or stenosis
a tricuspid valve disease AE that is asymptomatic; moderate regurgitation or stenosis by imaging
a tricuspid valve disease AE that is symptomatic; severe regurgitation or stenosis; symptoms controlled with medical intervention
a tricuspid valve disease AE that has life-threatening consequences; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., valve replacement, valvuloplasty)
an external ear inflammation AE that has external otitis with erythema or dry desquamation
